6402 /* */
6403 /* Ethernet MAC Registers bits definitions */
6404 /* */
6405 /******************************************************************************/
6406 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Control Register register */
6407 #define ETH_MACCR_WD ((uint32_t)0x00800000) /* Watchdog disable */
6408 #define ETH_MACCR_JD ((uint32_t)0x00400000) /* Jabber disable */
6409 #define ETH_MACCR_IFG ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Inter-frame gap */
6410 #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_96Bit ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 96Bit */
6411  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_88Bit ((uint32_t)0x00020000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 88Bit */
6412  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_80Bit ((uint32_t)0x00040000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 80Bit */
6413  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_72Bit ((uint32_t)0x00060000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 72Bit */
6414  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_64Bit ((uint32_t)0x00080000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 64Bit */
6415  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_56Bit ((uint32_t)0x000A0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 56Bit */
6416  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_48Bit ((uint32_t)0x000C0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 48Bit */
6417  #define ETH_MACCR_IFG_40Bit ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Minimum IFG between frames during transmission is 40Bit */
6418 #define ETH_MACCR_CSD ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Carrier sense disable (during transmission) */
6419 #define ETH_MACCR_FES ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* Fast ethernet speed */
6420 #define ETH_MACCR_ROD ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Receive own disable */
6421 #define ETH_MACCR_LM ((uint32_t)0x00001000) /* loopback mode */
6422 #define ETH_MACCR_DM ((uint32_t)0x00000800) /* Duplex mode */
6423 #define ETH_MACCR_IPCO ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* IP Checksum offload */
6424 #define ETH_MACCR_RD ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Retry disable */
6425 #define ETH_MACCR_APCS ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Automatic Pad/CRC stripping */
6426 #define ETH_MACCR_BL ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* Back-off limit: random integer number (r) of slot time delays before rescheduling
6427  a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */
6428  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_10 ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* k = min (n, 10) */
6429  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_8 ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /* k = min (n, 8) */
6430  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_4 ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* k = min (n, 4) */
6431  #define ETH_MACCR_BL_1 ((uint32_t)0x00000060) /* k = min (n, 1) */
6432 #define ETH_MACCR_DC ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* Defferal check */
6433 #define ETH_MACCR_TE ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* Transmitter enable */
6434 #define ETH_MACCR_RE ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* Receiver enable */
6435 
6436 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Frame Filter Register */
6437 #define ETH_MACFFR_RA ((uint32_t)0x80000000) /* Receive all */
6438 #define ETH_MACFFR_HPF ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* Hash or perfect filter */
6439 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAF ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Source address filter enable */
6440 #define ETH_MACFFR_SAIF ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /* SA inverse filtering */
6441 #define ETH_MACFFR_PCF ((uint32_t)0x000000C0) /* Pass control frames: 3 cases */
6442  #define ETH_MACFFR_PCF_BlockAll ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* MAC filters all control frames from reaching the application */
6443  #define ETH_MACFFR_PCF_ForwardAll ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* MAC forwards all control frames to application even if they fail the Address Filter */

6734 #define ETH_DMASR_TSTS ((uint32_t)0x20000000) /* Time-stamp trigger status */
6735 #define ETH_DMASR_PMTS ((uint32_t)0x10000000) /* PMT status */
6736 #define ETH_DMASR_MMCS ((uint32_t)0x08000000) /* MMC status */
6737 #define ETH_DMASR_EBS ((uint32_t)0x03800000) /* Error bits status */
6738  /* combination with EBS[2:0] for GetFlagStatus function */
6739  #define ETH_DMASR_EBS_DescAccess ((uint32_t)0x02000000) /* Error bits 0-data buffer, 1-desc. access */
6740  #define ETH_DMASR_EBS_ReadTransf ((uint32_t)0x01000000) /* Error bits 0-write trnsf, 1-read transfr */
6741  #define ETH_DMASR_EBS_DataTransfTx ((uint32_t)0x00800000) /* Error bits 0-Rx DMA, 1-Tx DMA */
6742 #define ETH_DMASR_TPS ((uint32_t)0x00700000) /* Transmit process state */
6743  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Stopped ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* Stopped - Reset or Stop Tx Command issued */
6744  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Fetching ((uint32_t)0x00100000) /* Running - fetching the Tx descriptor */
6745  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Waiting ((uint32_t)0x00200000) /* Running - waiting for status */
6746  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Reading ((uint32_t)0x00300000) /* Running - reading the data from host memory */
6747  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Suspended ((uint32_t)0x00600000) /* Suspended - Tx Descriptor unavailabe */
6748  #define ETH_DMASR_TPS_Closing ((uint32_t)0x00700000) /* Running - closing Rx descriptor */
6749 #define ETH_DMASR_RPS ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Receive process state */
6750  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Stopped ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* Stopped - Reset or Stop Rx Command issued */
6751  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Fetching ((uint32_t)0x00020000) /* Running - fetching the Rx descriptor */
6752  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Waiting ((uint32_t)0x00060000) /* Running - waiting for packet */
6753  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Suspended ((uint32_t)0x00080000) /* Suspended - Rx Descriptor unavailable */
6754  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Closing ((uint32_t)0x000A0000) /* Running - closing descriptor */
6755  #define ETH_DMASR_RPS_Queuing ((uint32_t)0x000E0000) /* Running - queuing the recieve frame into host memory */
6756 #define ETH_DMASR_NIS ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Normal interrupt summary */
6757 #define ETH_DMASR_AIS ((uint32_t)0x00008000) /* Abnormal interrupt summary */
6758 #define ETH_DMASR_ERS ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* Early receive status */
6759 #define ETH_DMASR_FBES ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Fatal bus error status */
6760 #define ETH_DMASR_ETS ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* Early transmit status */
6761 #define ETH_DMASR_RWTS ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Receive watchdog timeout status */
6762 #define ETH_DMASR_RPSS ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /* Receive process stopped status */
6763 #define ETH_DMASR_RBUS ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Receive buffer unavailable status */
6764 #define ETH_DMASR_RS ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* Receive status */
6765 #define ETH_DMASR_TUS ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /* Transmit underflow status */

6767 #define ETH_DMASR_TJTS ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* Transmit jabber timeout status */
6768 #define ETH_DMASR_TBUS ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* Transmit buffer unavailable status */
6769 #define ETH_DMASR_TPSS ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /* Transmit process stopped status */
6770 #define ETH_DMASR_TS ((uint32_t)0x00000001) /* Transmit status */

6772 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Operation Mode Register */
6773 #define ETH_DMAOMR_DTCEFD ((uint32_t)0x04000000) /* Disable Dropping of TCP/IP checksum error frames */
6774 #define ETH_DMAOMR_RSF ((uint32_t)0x02000000) /* Receive store and forward */
6775 #define ETH_DMAOMR_DFRF ((uint32_t)0x01000000) /* Disable flushing of received frames */
6776 #define ETH_DMAOMR_TSF ((uint32_t)0x00200000) /* Transmit store and forward */
6777 #define ETH_DMAOMR_FTF ((uint32_t)0x00100000) /* Flush transmit FIFO */
6778 #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC ((uint32_t)0x0001C000) /* Transmit threshold control */
6779  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_64Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 64 Bytes */
6780  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_128Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 128 Bytes */
6781  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_192Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00008000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 192 Bytes */
6782  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_256Bytes ((uint32_t)0x0000C000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 256 Bytes */
6783  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_40Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 40 Bytes */
6784  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_32Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00014000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 32 Bytes */
6785  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_24Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00018000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 24 Bytes */
6786  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_16Bytes ((uint32_t)0x0001C000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 16 Bytes */
6787 #define ETH_DMAOMR_ST ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Start/stop transmission command */
6788 #define ETH_DMAOMR_FEF ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Forward error frames */
6789 #define ETH_DMAOMR_FUGF ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* Forward undersized good frames */
6790 #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC ((uint32_t)0x00000018) /* receive threshold control */
6791  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_64Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 64 Bytes */
6792  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_32Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 32 Bytes */
6793  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_96Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 96 Bytes */
6794  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_128Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000018) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 128 Bytes */
6795 #define ETH_DMAOMR_OSF ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* operate on second frame */
6796 #define ETH_DMAOMR_SR ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /* Start/stop receive */

6849 #define SET_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) |= (BIT))
6850 
6851 #define CLEAR_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) &= ~(BIT))
6852 
6853 #define READ_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) & (BIT))
6854 
6855 #define CLEAR_REG(REG) ((REG) = (0x0))
6856 
6857 #define WRITE_REG(REG, VAL) ((REG) = (VAL))
6858 
6859 #define READ_REG(REG) ((REG))
6860 
6861 #define MODIFY_REG(REG, CLEARMASK, SETMASK) WRITE_REG((REG), (((READ_REG(REG)) & (~(CLEARMASK))) | (SETMASK)))
